  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The forward acceptance of the LHCb detector allows to probe proton and ion collisions in a unique kinematic range, complementary to the other LHC experiments. In the first part of these proceedings the production of <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>J</mi><mo stretchy="false">/</mo><mi>ψ</mi></math> and ϒ mesons decaying into two muons is presented. It has been studied with the LHCb experiment in proton-lead collisions at a proton-nucleon centre-of-mass energy <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><msqrt><msub><mrow><mi>s</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>N</mi><mi>N</mi></mrow></msub></msqrt><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn><mtext> TeV</mtext></math> . The nuclear modification factor and the forwardbackward production ratio have been determined for <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>J</mi><mo stretchy="false">/</mo><mi>ψ</mi></math> and <math altimg="si3.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi mathvariant="normal">ϒ</mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mn>1</mn><mi>S</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> mesons. In the second part the prospects are summarized to collect data with the LHCb detector in three additional configurations: the collection of data from lead-lead collisions, and the operation of the experiment in fixed-target mode, collecting data from collisions of the proton or lead beams with nuclei of a noble gas injected in the interaction region. The physics motivation for these additional data taking modes are presented.</subfield>
